<p>Using your own domain <span class="no-mobile">to direct short URLs & images</span> with 0tr.me is easy and <strong>free</strong> using some DNS magic! We're<span class="no-mobile"> going to assume you're</span> using Cloudflare<span class="no-mobile"> for this, but most DNS providers have a similar setup and this should work fine with them</span>.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Launch <span class="no-mobile">your</span> <a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com">Cloudflare <span class="no-mobile">Dashboard</span></a> and choose the site you want <span class="no-mobile">to use</span> for <span class="no-mobile">0tr.me</span> short URLs
  <br>
<img class="imgDir" src="https://cdn.glitch.global/65f2254a-8e40-4b88-aae8-bb42a288bd4d/Screenshot%202023-03-23%20at%2010.10.48%20PM.png?v=1679625176445">
    
  </li>
  <li>
Navigate to DNS and add a new DNS record<span class="no-mobile">. Set TTL to auto if needed</span>:

